# epub-converter: Documentation Sync

When modifying any file in `epub-converter/`, always update **all** related docs to stay in sync.

## What to check after every change

| If you change...                  | Then update...                                               |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| CLI flags in `convert.py`         | Docstring in `convert.py`, CLI Flags table in `CONTEXT.md`, examples in `docker-compose.yml` comments |
| Dependencies (imports)            | `requirements.txt`, Dependencies table in `CONTEXT.md`       |
| Volume mount paths                | `docker-compose.yml`, path detection in `convert.py`, Volume Mounts table in `CONTEXT.md` |
| Output path or structure          | Output Structure section in `CONTEXT.md`, docstring in `convert.py` |
| EPUB structure (cover, TOC, etc.) | EPUB Structure section in `CONTEXT.md`                       |
| AUDIT.md section format           | AUDIT.md Integration section in `CONTEXT.md`                 |
| Files added or removed            | Files table in `CONTEXT.md`, `COPY` line in `Dockerfile`     |

## Cross-file consistency rules

1. **`convert.py` docstring** must list the same flags as `argparse` definitions below it
2. **`CONTEXT.md` CLI Flags table** must match `argparse` in `convert.py` exactly
3. **`CONTEXT.md` Dependencies table** must match `requirements.txt` exactly
4. **`CONTEXT.md` Volume Mounts table** must match `docker-compose.yml` volumes exactly
5. **`CONTEXT.md` Files table** must list every file in `epub-converter/`
6. **`docker-compose.yml` examples** in comments must match actual CLI flags
7. **`Dockerfile` COPY** must include all `.py` files used at runtime
8. **`convert.py` path detection** (Docker vs local) must reference the same mount paths as `docker-compose.yml`

## Quick checklist

- [ ] `requirements.txt` matches actual imports across all `.py` files
- [ ] `CONTEXT.md` tables are all current
- [ ] `convert.py` docstring matches argparse
- [ ] `docker-compose.yml` comment examples match argparse
- [ ] `Dockerfile` COPY includes all source files
- [ ] No unused imports in `.py` files
